                        <li xml:id="auto_nznnag6f"><p xml:id="auto_lc1v8o3p"><m>V = 3.14 \times (0.4)^2 \times 1.2 = 3.14 \times 0.16 \times 1.2 \approx 0.603\,\text{m}^3 \approx 603</m> litres.</p></li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_b2gt6ion"><p xml:id="auto_s7c9fih6">Accept any two reasonable examples, e.g. planning water storage for households and farms; determining how much grain a container can hold; calculating fuel capacity for transport; estimating materials needed for construction.</p></li>
